Pandanus julianettii

    Authority   Martelli
      Family    Liliopsida:Arecidae:Pandanales:Pandanaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 8245

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION An evergreen, erect, sparsely branched, woody plant,
   with large leathery leaves. It can reach a height of 1-20 m. USES It is
   grown for its edible seeds and for the production of textile fibres.
   The seeds are oily and contain a fair amount of protein. KILLING T May
   tolerate 0째C for short and 3째C for prolonged periods. GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial woody plant, that can be harvested first time 6-8 years from
   planting, with an economical life of 20-40 years and with a total
   lifespan of up to 70 years. Require 90-120 days from flowering to
   fruiting and have no obvious seasonality. COMMON NAMES Pandanus,
   Karuka, Screw-pine, Anga, Amsal. FURTHER INF Pandanus can be found at
   altitudes up to 1300-3300 m at 6째S. and in New Guinea at elevations
   between 1700 and 2900 m. Latitudinal range is 5-7째S. It is adapted to
   humid conditions.

   Sources
   SOURCES (P. julianettii Martel)
   Rose C 1986 [RAIN, TEMP, LIG, DEP, DRA, PH, SAL, TEXT, FER]
   Sims D (pers. comm.)
   Purseglove J 1972 pp 512 [USE]
   Paijmans K 1976 pp 132
   Verheij E 1991 pp 242-243 [USE]

